    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nIs sandbox or \"restricted mode\" actually doing anything useful? The need for a pseudo \"secure\" mode is outdated since:\r\n\r\n1. 'modeline' no longer allows expressions (unless 'modelineexpr' is set, but we could remove that in favor of 'exrc')\r\n2. 'exrc' has per-directory opt-in (`:trust`)\r\n\r\nUse cases for sandbox:\r\n\r\n- vimgolf? https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/11972#issuecomment-757536989\r\n\r\nPrevious:\r\n\r\n- https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/11972\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n- Remove 'secure' option.\r\n- Remove 'modelineexpr' option.\r\n- Remove \"sandbox\" concept and `:sandbox` command.\r\n- Remove `check_secure` function.",
    "closed_at": null,
